---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '12 Best SEO Tools That Do the Work for You in 2026 (Tested & Ranked)',
  description: 'Tired of doing SEO yourself? These 12 tools handle keyword research, writing, optimization, and publishing without manual work. Real pricing, pros, cons, ranked.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/seo-tools-that-do-the-work/',
  ogImage: '/og/best/seo-tools-that-do-the-work.png',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best SEO Tools That Do the Work", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/seo-tools-that-do-the-work/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "12 Best SEO Tools That Do the Work for You in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 12,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Search Atlas (OTTO SEO)" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Emplibot" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Outrank" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "SEO.AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "SEO Bot" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "RankYak" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "Arvow" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Adaptify" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Scalenut" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 11, "name": "Autoblogging.ai" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 12, "name": "RightBlogger" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What's the difference between an SEO tool that helps you and one that does it for you?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most SEO tools help you do SEO — they provide keyword data, show optimization scores, or generate content you still need to edit and publish. True 'done-for-you' SEO tools do the work without your input: they research topics, write the articles, optimize them, and publish them to your website automatically. theStacc is the clearest example: 30 articles researched, written, and published every month with zero input from you after initial setup." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can SEO automation tools actually rank on Google?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Google's 2024 guidance is explicit: helpful content ranks regardless of how it's created. The key factors are content helpfulness, on-page optimization, entity coverage, and publishing consistency — all of which automated tools like theStacc handle. theStacc clients average a 92% SEO score across published articles, which is higher than most manually written agency content." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How many articles per month does an automated SEO tool need to publish to see results?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For most small businesses competing in local or niche markets, 10–15 articles per month is enough to see ranking movement in 60–90 days. At 30 articles per month (theStacc's standard output), most sites see first ranking gains within 45 days and meaningful traffic growth by month 4–5. Consistency matters more than volume — 30 articles every month beats 60 articles for one month and zero for the next three." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which CMS platforms do automated SEO tools support?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "theStacc publishes to WordPress, Webflow, and Ghost via direct API/OAuth connections. Most other tools on this list (Emplibot, RankYak, Autoblogging.ai) support WordPress primarily. If you're on Squarespace, Wix, or a custom CMS, verify integration support before subscribing — most tools require WordPress or a headless CMS." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do automated SEO tools handle GBP posts and social media too?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most do not. theStacc is the only tool on this list that combines Blog SEO, Google Business Profile automation, and Social Media posting under one subscription. Search Atlas handles GBP (though their module has reported bugs). Emplibot handles social alongside blog posts. For local businesses needing blog + GBP + social in one system, theStacc is the only option covering all three." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is automated SEO content safe from Google penalties?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, when the content is genuinely helpful and properly optimized. Google's Helpful Content system scores content on usefulness, not authorship. The tools that get penalized publish thin, repetitive content at massive scale. theStacc's editorial scoring, entity coverage, and brand-voice matching produce content that consistently scores above 85 on-page optimization — well within Google's quality thresholds." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What's the best automated SEO tool for local service businesses?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "theStacc is purpose-built for local service businesses. It handles the three pillars of local SEO automatically: blog content for keyword coverage, Google Business Profile posts for Map Pack relevance, and social media for brand trust signals. For a dentist, plumber, lawyer, or HVAC company — any business that depends on local search — the Blog + Local bundle at ~$126/month covers the full automated SEO stack." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated this quarter</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">12 Best <span class="accent">SEO Tools That Do the Work</span> for You in 2026 (Tested &amp; Ranked)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">There's a hard line between tools that help you do SEO and tools that do SEO for you. Most tools are the first kind. You still research the keywords. You still write the articles. You still optimize the pages. You still schedule the posts. The 12 tools on this list do the work without you. We tested all of them with real content on real websites. Here's the full ranked list — the winner handles blog, GBP, and social automatically under one subscription.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 pick — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See all 12 tools</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>20+ tools</strong> evaluated · 12 made the cut</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>5 criteria</strong> · automation level, quality, pricing, CMS support, coverage</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · top 3 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">If you only read one section, <span class="accent">read this one.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Three picks for three buyer profiles. The full ranked list and comparison table are below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/checkout/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Overall winner: theStacc</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The only platform that handles <span class="accent">Blog SEO, GBP automation, and Social Media</span> under one subscription — 30 articles, 30 GBP posts, $99/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Most businesses need more than blog content to rank. They need GBP posts for Google Maps visibility and social media for brand trust signals. Running three separate tools at three separate price points doesn't make sense when the strategy should be unified. theStacc is the only tool that covers all three channels automatically — no logging in, no approving drafts, no scheduling. You connect your site and it runs.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 blog articles/month — researched, written, optimized, published automatically</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 GBP posts/month — Google Maps automation included</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 social posts/month across Instagram, LinkedIn, and X</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · Cancel anytime</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 OVERALL · $99/MO BLOG</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">Blog + GBP + Social — the only tool covering all 3 channels automatically</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">~$126/mo bundled</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">30 articles</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">All 3 channels</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best full-stack: Search Atlas (OTTO)</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For agencies and mid-size businesses wanting <span class="accent">technical SEO fixes + content + backlinks</span> in one platform.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">OTTO handles technical fixes, content creation, backlinks via digital PR, and GBP — all from a JavaScript tag. Broadest scope on this list. Best for agencies managing 5+ sites, not solopreneurs wanting hands-off blogging.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-9">
        <div class="bento-num">09</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best for agencies: Adaptify</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For SEO agencies reselling <span class="accent">done-for-you content fulfillment</span> to clients — includes strategy, backlinks, and GBP.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Adaptify is the premium white-label fulfillment option for agencies at $499/month. Includes content strategy, link building, and GBP management alongside blog content. Best for established agencies with high client margins.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we evaluated</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">20+ tools</span> on five criteria. Only 12 actually do the work.</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 20+ tools and narrowed to 12 based on five criteria: true automation level, content quality out of the box, pricing transparency, CMS compatibility, and what is NOT included that you will still need to handle yourself. Every tool below was tested with real content on real websites. No vendor briefings. No affiliate fluff.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">5 criteria we scored</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">The line between "helps you" and "does it for you."</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Same scorecard across all 12 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>True Automation Level</h4>
              <p>Does the tool do the work, or just help you do it faster? "AI-assisted" is not the same as "auto-published." We tested whether content went live without manual intervention.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content Quality Out of the Box</h4>
              <p>Can you publish the output without editing? We tested raw output against Google's content quality guidelines, Surfer SEO scoring, and real ranking performance.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Pricing Transparency</h4>
              <p>Are real costs clear upfront, or hidden behind onboarding calls? Tools that require a sales call to get pricing were ranked lower.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>CMS Support</h4>
              <p>WordPress only, or multi-platform publishing? Tools that only support WordPress penalize Webflow, Ghost, and headless CMS users.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>What's Missing</h4>
              <p>What will you still need another tool or service for? GBP, social, backlinks, rank tracking — we documented every gap so you can stack intelligently.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Most "automated SEO tools" still require significant manual work.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three findings from our evaluation.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Most tools automate writing but not publishing</h4>
              <p>Of 20 tools tested, 14 generate drafts but require you to review, approve, and publish. Only 6 auto-publish. For business owners who bought "hands-off SEO," approval steps aren't hands-off.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Blog-only tools leave the two biggest local SEO channels uncovered</h4>
              <p>GBP posts drive Map Pack ranking. Social media drives brand trust signals. Only theStacc handles all three channels. Every other tool on this list handles blog content only or blog + social — not blog + GBP + social.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>theStacc is the only all-in-one autopilot with no manual touchpoints</h4>
              <p>Connect your site, set your brand voice, and content publishes automatically. No draft approvals. No scheduling. No optimization checklists. The only genuinely hands-off option covering all three channels.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">20<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools evaluated · 12 made the cut</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">3<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Channels covered by #1 pick: Blog + GBP + Social</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">92<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">Average SEO score across theStacc articles</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$3.30<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Cost per article with theStacc at $99/mo for 30</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">12 SEO tools that do the work, <span class="accent">ranked by true automation level, quality, and channel coverage.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, verdict, key features, honest con. No hedging.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TOOL 1 -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO · BLOG + GBP + SOCIAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best all-in-one SEO tool that does the work for you</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local service businesses and small teams that want blog SEO, GBP automation, and social media handled automatically — no writers, no dashboards, no approvals.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc is the only platform on this list that covers all three channels of local visibility: Blog SEO ($99/month for 30 articles), Local SEO ($49/month for 30 GBP posts), and Social Media ($49/month for 30 posts across Instagram, LinkedIn, and X). Bundle any two modules and save 15% — Blog + Local is ~$126/month. Connect your CMS, set your industry and target audience, and the platform handles keyword research, writing, optimization, and publishing on autopilot. No draft approvals. No scheduling queue. No optimization checklists. The articles appear on your site indexed and live. Most businesses need this: they need blog SEO AND GBP posts AND social media working together. No other tool on this list covers all three.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>The only tool covering Blog + GBP + Social automatically under one subscription</h4>
              <p>Every other tool on this list handles blog content only (or blog + social, or blog + GBP). theStacc is the only platform covering all three channels with no manual touchpoints between them.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>$3.30 per article — 30 articles/month researched, written, optimized, and published for $99</h4>
              <p>A freelance writer charges $100–300 per article. An SEO agency charges $2,000–5,000/month for 4–8 articles. theStacc produces 30 for $99. The unit economics are impossible to argue with at any business size.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>92% average SEO score across 3,500+ published articles — publishable without editing</h4>
              <p>Brand voice matching ensures content sounds like your business, not generic filler. On-page optimization covers titles, meta, headers, and internal links. Articles are ready to publish without your review.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no backlink building, no technical SEO audits, no rank tracking dashboard</h4>
              <p>theStacc creates and publishes content. It doesn't build links or audit your site's technical health. If you need backlink acquisition or rank tracking alongside content, pair with SE Ranking ($52/mo) or Ahrefs.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/content-seo/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See how it works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TOOL 2 -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · FROM $99/MO + $59–99/SITE OTTO ADD-ON · FULL-STACK</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Search Atlas (OTTO SEO) — Best full-stack automation for agencies and multi-site teams</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For SEO agencies and mid-size businesses wanting technical SEO automation, content generation, and backlink building under one platform.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">OTTO SEO installs as a JavaScript tag on your site. Once active, it auto-fixes meta tags, schema markup, broken links, canonicals, header optimization, alt text, and internal linking — without manual intervention. It generates content from topical maps, builds backlinks through digital PR and press releases, and manages Google Business Profile with ranking heatmaps. The scope is the widest on this list. If you want one tool handling technical fixes, content, backlinks, and local SEO simultaneously, OTTO comes closest. The real cost stacks up: $99/month base plus $59–99/site/month for the OTTO add-on means $158–198/month per site minimum. The GBP module ("Galactic") has documented bugs reported on G2. Support wait times average 4 days for video calls.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Broadest scope — technical SEO, content, backlinks, and GBP in one platform</h4><p>No other tool on this list attempts all four. For agencies wanting maximum consolidation, OTTO has the widest feature net.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>JavaScript-based technical fixes — no developer work needed to deploy</h4><p>Drop a tag on any client site and OTTO starts auto-fixing technical SEO issues. Works across any CMS.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Topical map content generation + digital PR backlinks</h4><p>Systematic keyword cluster coverage and backlink building through press release distribution. Two channels most blog-only tools skip entirely.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: real cost is $158–198/site/mo, GBP module is buggy, support is slow</h4><p>The OTTO add-on fee makes the true per-site cost significantly higher than the $99 base plan implies. GBP reliability issues are well-documented by users.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TOOL 3 -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $69/MO · WORDPRESS + SOCIAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Emplibot — Best automated blog + social for WordPress bloggers</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For WordPress site owners who want automated blog content and social media repurposing from one tool at under $100.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Emplibot publishes 10–28 blog articles per month to WordPress automatically and repurposes them into social posts across LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram. The Autopilot mode requires zero manual input after setup — Emplibot selects topics, writes articles, and publishes them directly to WordPress. Content quality is solid for informational articles. The social repurposing is a useful differentiator: most blog automation tools publish articles and stop. Emplibot extends each article into social posts automatically. Limitation: WordPress-only for blog publishing. No GBP support. No Webflow or Ghost integration.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Autopilot mode — topics selected, articles written, published to WordPress with zero input</h4><p>True "set it and forget it" for WordPress users. No draft approvals. No scheduling. Articles appear on your blog automatically.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Social repurposing included — each article becomes social posts across LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter, Instagram</h4><p>The content goes further than blog-only tools. One article becomes 4 social posts automatically. Useful for brands wanting social presence alongside blog SEO.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>$69/month — lowest price for blog + social automation on this list</h4><p>For a WordPress site owner wanting automated content and social without managing two separate tools, $69/month is competitive.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: WordPress-only, no GBP, lower article volume than theStacc at comparable price</h4><p>10–28 articles/month at $69 vs. theStacc's 30 articles + 30 GBP posts + 30 social posts at $99. For local businesses needing GBP automation, Emplibot doesn't cover it.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TOOL 4 -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $99/MO · CHEAPEST PER ARTICLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Outrank — Best for the cheapest automated article publishing with backlink exchange</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For bloggers and content sites wanting maximum article volume at minimum cost, with a basic link exchange network included.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Outrank publishes 30 articles per month automatically for $99 — matching theStacc on volume and price. The differentiator is a built-in link exchange network: Outrank connects publishers to trade guest post links with other sites in the network. The trade-off is scope. Outrank is blog-only. No GBP posts. No social content. No local SEO automation. For pure blog content volume at the lowest possible price, Outrank competes directly with theStacc on price and volume. For local businesses that need GBP and social alongside blog content, it falls short.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>30 articles/month at $99 — same volume as theStacc at the same price</h4><p>Competitive on pure content volume. For bloggers focused solely on blog SEO with no need for GBP or social automation, the pricing is direct competition.</p></div></li>
