  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Buyer's guide</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">How to choose an <span class="accent">SEO tool that does the work for you.</span></h2>
      <p>If you're evaluating beyond this list, here's the scorecard we'd use ourselves. The five questions that separate true autopilot tools from AI-assisted tools with marketing copy about automation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Ask specifically: does content publish without my approval, or do I review drafts?</h4>
              <p>Most "automated" tools generate drafts you still approve. True autopilot tools publish without your input. If you need to log in and click "approve" for each article, it's assisted writing, not automation. Ask directly: "Does content publish to my site without any action from me?"</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Count the channels — blog-only tools leave GBP and social uncovered</h4>
              <p>For local businesses, blog content alone isn't enough. GBP posts drive Map Pack ranking. Social posts drive brand trust. If you're considering a blog-only tool, budget separately for GBP automation and social scheduling — or pick theStacc and cover all three in one subscription.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Verify your CMS is supported before subscribing</h4>
              <p>Most tools require WordPress. If you're on Webflow, Ghost, or a custom CMS, your options narrow significantly. theStacc supports WordPress, Webflow, and Ghost via direct API. Verify integration compatibility before committing to any monthly subscription.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Calculate annual keyword footprint, not monthly article count</h4>
              <p>4 articles/month × 12 = 48 new indexed pages per year. 30 articles/month × 12 = 360. The traffic compound effect of 360 versus 48 indexed pages at 12 months is not linear — it's exponential. Volume matters for keyword coverage.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Test brand voice quality before committing — generic content won't represent your business well</h4>
              <p>Run a $1 trial and read the first three articles. Do they sound like a human wrote them for your business, or like generic AI output? Brand voice training is what separates publishable content from content you'd be embarrassed to have on your site.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
